items.text: caught and bowled! Back of a length on off, and this is too close to his body. He slogs rather uncomfortably, and takes a leading edge. The ball's in the air for a while, and Hasan Ali runs forward towards the batsman, and then takes the easiest of catches. Mithun falls after a fighting innings.

items.postText: Anand: "Is Kayes the right batsman to come out now ?? Would have preferred Mahmudullah, given him ample time to set in and go big in the last 5-6 overs. Never saw Kayes as a aggressive batsman. Without Shakib bowling, B'Desh needs every last run they can get to defend against Pak." -- Think Kayes isn't as good a finisher. Therefore they're using him now, instead of later.

items.preText: Shadab's back. He's got four overs left.
items.text: full on middle stump, and skidding straight through! Kayes is on the back foot, and the ball hits his front leg as he tries to defend. Shadab appeals and the umpire raises his finger. Kayes asks Mushfiqur about reviewing but the senior batsman tells him to walk back. Smart choice, one reckons.
